Go examines git state to decide if polecat removal is safe:
```go
status, err := polecatGit.CheckUncommittedWork()
if status.StashCount > 0 || status.UnpushedCommits > 0 {
    return &UncommittedWorkError{...}
}
```

**ZFC-compliant solution:**
Polecat reports its own cleanup status via agent bead:
- state: stopped
- cleanup_status: clean | has_uncommitted | has_stash | has_unpushed
- Witness reads cleanup_status before calling nuke
- Polecat is authority on whether it's safe to remove

**Relates to:** Day 4.1/4.2 (recycle/nuke commands)

